All Classes

  • Class Description
    Automaton
    This class is the actual Automaton that will implement almost all other classes in the program
    AutomatonMeasurements
    This class shouldn't be instantiated, but rather its static methods can be called to get some information about an Automaton
    AutomatonMeasurementsTest  
    AutomatonTest  
    BoundaryConditions  
    Cell
    This is the most basic unit of the Automaton, and only has one data member which holds whether it is in the OFF or ON state
    CellState
    This enum type allows a Cell to either be in an OFF or ON state, which with a corresponding character('.' and 'O' respectively)
    CellStateTest  
    CellTest  
    CircularBoundaryConditions
    The CircularBoundary condition basically wraps the Generation into a circle, meaning the left most Cell's left neighbor is the right most Cell and the right most Cell's right neighbor is the left most Cell
    CircularBoundaryConditionsTest  
    Driver  
    ElementaryRule
    This Rule evolves a Cell based on its current state as well as the states of its left and right neighbors.
    ElementaryRuleTest  
    EvolvedCell
    This class extends the Cell class and will make up any Generation of the Automaton that has been evolved.
    EvolvedCellTest  
    FixedBoundaryConditions
    The FixedBoundary condition sets a fixed state for the neighbors of Cells at the edge of the Generation
    FixedBoundaryConditionsTest  
    Generation
    This class represents the state of an Automaton, holding an array of many Cell or EvolvedCell objects
    GenerationTest  
    InvalidRuleNumException  
    InvalidStepNumException  
    Rule
    This class is an abstract class that can be extended to create specific rules the Automaton will follow when evolving
    TotalisticRule
    This Rule evolves a Cell based on how many Cells in a radius(which is 2 for this program) are ON.
    TotalisticRuleTest
